-- ECC Awarded $400 Million Contract to Upgrade Ghana Water System
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-09-03T14:07:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-03/ecc-awarded-400-million-contract-to-upgrade-ghana-water-system.html
ECC won a $400 million contract to
upgrade and revamp  Ghana ’s national water system for Ghana Water
Co., the Burlingame, California-based company said.  The project is being financed by a U.S. Export-Import Bank
loan to Ghana’s government and partners to ECC under the
contract include  General Electric Co. (GE) , ECC said in a  statement.
Work is slated to begin this year and end in 2018.  “This effort will provide state-of-the-art technology from
GE to the highest priority areas of need through a partnership
between our team and the Ghana Water Co.,” ECC Vice President
Richard Ebel said in the Sept. 1 statement.  Founded in 1985, ECC clients include the U.S. Departments
of Defense, Energy and State as well as the  Asian Development
Bank  and other international agencies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
